                <head>56. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_PC1">Christian Pineau</persName> came to
                    the United States on November 17 to take part in the debate on Algeria in the
                    U.N. General Assembly. He visted Washington November 18–20. Memoranda of his
                    conversations with Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> on
                    November 19 on the Tunisian arms question and on the Algerian debate in the
                    United Nations are printed in volume XVIII, pages 764 and 285, respectively. The
                    draft of a memorandum for the record of <persName corresp="#p_PC1"
                        >Pineau</persName>’s conversation with Secretary of Defense <persName
                        corresp="#p_MENH1">McElroy</persName> on November 20 is printed <ref
                        target="#d57">
                        <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>
                    </ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
